	(5, 1, '20 Best AngularJS Development Tools for Developers', '20-best-angularjs-development-tools-for-developers', '<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Angular has turned out to be a boon in developing a dynamic web page. As we all know developing code with a barefoot is always being a tedious task to do. AngularJS Developer is assisted with the efficient bundle of tools to help every developer to work in an efficient manner within a less period of time.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Let us discuss some of the amazing tools which are available for&nbsp;<a href="https://www.angularminds.com/angularjs-development-company.html" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-href="https://www.angularminds.com/angularjs-development-company.html">Web Application Development</a>, using AngularJS for developing web pages in a very smart and efficient way.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">List of Testing Tools For AngularJS</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #00ff00;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Karma:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">It is a Spectacular Test Runner for JavaScript. As we all know, No product can be launched before it is tested and there cannot be any good tool other than Karma which makes testing an easier task for us. With Karma, testing can be on the real browsers and mobile devices such as handsets and tablets.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Protractor:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">It is a Node.js program is build on top of WebDriverJS. Protractor runs on the real browsers which also provides with the end to end testing.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Jasmine:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Provides a testing environment for the Node.js projects. It works whenever java-scripts implemented.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Mocha.js&nbsp;:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">It is a component rich JavaScript test system that keeps running on node.js and the browser and permits asynchronous testing making it adaptable with announcing and mapping.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Text Editors</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">SublimeText:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Developers prefers using this text editor as it helps with easy coding.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Angular GetText:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">This works as a magic stick for the developers as it provides translation support for Angular. we can easily convert any language using this tool like test in English can easily convert into browser or local language.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Webstorm:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">It is one of the best AngularJS IDE and text. A smart code editor providing great support for JavaScript, Node.js, HTML and CSS and also its gears are oiled for all other modern technology successors. Developers prefer using Webstrom editors commonly.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Code Orchestra:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">This is a dynamic tool which helps to build front-end which allows you to write code live-style. When you modify the code and save it. The result is implement at that point automatically on the working application using few protocols.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Speed Drivers For AngularJS Development</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Angular Kickstart:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">This enables speedy AngularJS development services. This helps developers slid easily through the development phase.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Angular Seed:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">This is a blueprint for your typical AngularJS web app and is you can apply to quickly bootstrap the angular app projects along with the dev environment for these projects.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">AngularJS UI:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Speed and Project deployment duration are the key factors which makes AngularJS one of the favorite technology among the developers and the users. And here comes the Angular UI into the picture. It helps to speed up the process with the use of directives which can be integrate with UI-Bootstrap. Directives are like ui-map, ui-calendar and ui-router.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Development Optimizing Tools</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Ment.io:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">This tools jQuery independent which provides programmers flexibility. This tool also supports mentions and macros widget.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Djangular:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">It is a reusable application furnishing better application reconciliation with AngularJS.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">AngularFire:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">It provides with flexible API and 3-way data binding, and rapid development capabilities ease development. This helps to easily develop back end to your Angular app.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Restangular:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">This tool is ideal where the Web app consumes a large chunk of data from REST API. It simplifies common GET, POST, DELETE, and UPDATES requests and also requires minimum client code.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Generator Angular:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">It helps to set with all the necessary boiler points ready for the developing process of your web app. Places all the required defaults on the starting point.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">NG-Inspector:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Enables your browsers with an inspector pane which helps you in developing, debugging and understanding your AngularJS applications. Uses Controllers and Directives for identifying and displaying scope.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Mean:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">We can call this tool as a perfect reusable unit of code that AngularJS developers use to create MongoDB, Node.js, Express, and Angular apps. Consist of configured modules such as Mongoose and Passport</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Angular Deckgrid:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">When directive doesn&rsquo;t depend on their visual representation this tool provides with the grid to the AngularJS. It uses CSS file for all the visual representation.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Videogular:</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">AngularJS project can feature HTML5-based video playing capabilities that translate to an easy to implement video player for your design. It caters AngularJS with videos and other multimedia elements in your app with ease.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">If you are just starting with your AngularJs development or any endeavor is set to&nbsp;<a href="https://www.angularminds.com/hire-resources/hire-angularjs-developers.html" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener" data-href="https://www.angularminds.com/hire-resources/hire-angularjs-developers.html">Hire AngularJs developers</a>&nbsp;those set of tools are going to make their developing experience smooth and cake way throughout the process.</span></p>', '1510047462.jpeg', 'Y', 1, '2017-11-07 13:07:45', '2017-11-08 10:09:22', NULL),
	(6, 1, '6 Best PHP Frameworks for Modern Web Developers in 2017', '6-best-php-frameworks-for-modern-web-developers-in-2017', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #008080;"><strong>Laravel Framework</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Coming in at number 1 on our list, is Laravel.&nbsp;<a href="https://laravel.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Laravel</a>&nbsp;is a comprehensive framework designed for rapidly building applications using the MVC architecture. Laravel is currently the most popular PHP framework, with a huge community of developers.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">It features tons of laravel specific packages, the lightweight Blade templating engine, unit testing, ORM, a packaging system, RESTful controllers, and now Laravel is the first framework to introduce routing in a abstract way.It takes out the hassle of code organization.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Queue management is also a feature that handles tasks in the background and then logs the activity for you all while tasks are normally run in the frontend. Packages can be easily added with the robust Composer built in to Laravel. It integrates with Gulp and Elixir so any npm packages and bower packages can be called directly via ssh.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">One of the best things Laravel handles well are noSQL structures like&nbsp;<a href="http://coderseye.com/learn-mongodb-tutorials-as-a-beginner/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MongoDB</a>&nbsp;or Redis. It&rsquo;s easy to get started with Laravel thanks to its extensive documentation, popularity, and Laravel Udemy: popular videos and tutorials meant to get developers new to Laravel up and running.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">We have looked for the most comprehensive&nbsp;<strong>free</strong>&nbsp;PHP course for our readers and found the folks at Team Treehouse do by far the best job. You can sign up for free and start learning how to be a PHP pro.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #008080;"><strong>Phalcon Framework</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Phalcon is a MVC based PHP framework, uniquely built as C-extension, meaning it&rsquo;s absolutely blazing fast. Phalcon uses very few resources in comparison to other frameworks, translating into very fast processing of HTTP requests, which can be critical for developers working with systems that don&rsquo;t offer much overhead.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Phalcon has been actively developed since 2012, and includes ORM, MVC, caching, and auto-loading components. Its latest and first long term support release includes support for PHP 7.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Phalcon brings developers data storage tools such as its own SQL dialect: PHQL, as well as Object Document Mapping for MongoDB. Other features include Template engines, form builders, ease of building applications with international language support, and more. Phalcon is ideal for building both performance REST APIs, as well as full-fledged web applications.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Download and Info:&nbsp;<a href="https://phalconphp.com/en/" rel="nofollow">https://phalconphp.com/en/</a></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #008080;"><strong>Codeigniter&nbsp;Framework</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Codeigniter is an ideal framework for rapid application development. It&rsquo;s a lightweight, low-hassle, framework with a small footprint that can be installed just by uploading it directly to your hosting. No special command line or software installation is required. Upload the files and you&rsquo;re ready to go.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Building full fledged web applications is a breeze with it&rsquo;s small learning curve, and numerous libraries. Speaking of east of development, Codeigniter&rsquo;s documentations is extensive, and it&rsquo;s community is vast and very helpful. Code Igniter is backed by a academic entity as well: The British Columbia Institute of Technology, which will help ensure it&rsquo;s continued development and growth.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Feature-wise, Codeigniter comes with many built in libraries for unit testing, form validation, email, sessions, and much more! If you can&rsquo;t find a library you&rsquo;re looking for, it&rsquo;s also pretty easy to build your own, and then share it with the community.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Download and Info:&nbsp;<a href="https://www.codeigniter.com/" rel="nofollow">https://www.codeigniter.com/</a></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #008080;"><strong>Symfony&nbsp;Framework</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Symfony has been touted for a while now as a very stable, high performance, well documented, and modular project. Symfony is backed by the French SensioLabs, and has been developed by them and it&rsquo;s community to be a fantastic framework.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Symfony is used by many big name companies like the BBC and open source project such as Drupal and eZpublish. Symfony was written with stability in mind in a very professional way. It&rsquo;s documentation is extensive, and it&rsquo;s community is just as vast. building both performance REST APIs, as well as full fledged web applications.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Download and Info:&nbsp;<a href="https://symfony.com/" rel="nofollow">https://symfony.com/</a></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #008080;"><strong>CakePHP&nbsp;Framework</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;Cakephp is an ideal framework for beginners and for rapidly developing commercial web apps. It comes with code generation and scaffolding functionality to speed up the development process, while also bringing in tons of packages to take care of common functionality.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">It&rsquo;s unique in having MVC conventions that help guide the development process. Configuration is also a breeze as it removes the need for complicated XML or YAML config files. Builds are fast and its security features include measures to prevent XSS, SQL Injection, CSRF, and tools for form validation.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">CakePHP is under active development with good documentation and lots of support portals to help get started. Premium Support is also an option for developers who choose to use Cakephp, via the Cake Development Corporation.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Download and Info:&nbsp;<a href="http://cakephp.org/" rel="nofollow">http://cakephp.org/</a></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: #008080;"><strong>Zend Framework</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Zend Framework is a popular, go-to professional framework commonly used for high-performance enterprise-level applications. Zend is built with security, performance, and extensibility in mind.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Because of it&rsquo;s focus for enterprise applications, it has tons of components for authentication, feeds, forms, services and more. Because of its enterprise driven nature, Zend isn&rsquo;t ideal for rapid application development, though it does come with tools to make a developer&rsquo;s life easier, including Zend&rsquo;s proprietary IDE: Zend Studio. Which neatly integrates with Zend Framework.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Download and Info:&nbsp;<a href="https://framework.zend.com/" rel="nofollow">https://framework.zend.com/</a></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Refrence: <a href="https://www.sitepoint.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SitePoint</a></span></p>', '1510056068.png', 'Y', 1, '2017-11-07 15:31:09', '2017-11-13 21:14:52', NULL),
	(7, 1, 'بررسی : آیفون 10؛ رودرروی آینده', 'بررسی-آیفون-10-رودرروی-آینده', '<p dir="rtl" style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">قبل از تولد اولین آیفون همه تلفن های هوشمند صفحه کلید داشتند تا اینکه اپل در سال ۲۰۰۷ نشان داد وجود تنها یک دکمه می تواند برای ساخت موبایل کافی باشد. پس از آن، تا ۱۰ سال شاهد تکرار همین رویه بودیم. در همین سالها تولید کنندگان رقیب به مرور حاشیه های اطراف صفحه نمایش را تا جای ممکن کاهش دادند و حسگر را به پشت بدنه منتقل کردند، اما اپل روی حضور دکمه هوم در حاشیه نه چندان باریک پایین صفحه نمایش اصرار داشت. حالا بالاخره در دهمین سالگرد تولید آیفون، همان یک دکمه هم کنار گذاشته شده و اپل محصول جدید خود را به نمایش گذاشته است: موبایلی که دکمه هوم و حتی حسگر اثر انگشت ندارد.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="rtl" style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: tahoma, arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">موبایل جدید اپل قفل دستگاه را به جای اثر انگشت شما با اسکن کردن چهره باز می کند و برای استفاده از آن، کارکرد دکمه هوم با سوایپ کردن روی صفحه جایگزین شده است. اپل می خواهد با آیفون ۱۰ شما را به آینده منتقل کند، جایی که مثل فیلم های علمی تخیلی یک صفحه نمایش را در دست گرفته انگشت خود را به شکلی روی آن حرکت می دهید که تعجب بیننده را بر می انگیزد. البته اگر نمی خواهید برای رفتن به آینده ۱۰۰۰ دلار هزینه کنید یا هنوز برای کنار گذاشتن دکمه هوم تمایل ندارید، اپل برای شما آیفون ۸ و ۸ پلاس (<a href="http://digiato.com/article/2017/09/26/%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%B1%D8%B3%DB%8C-%D8%AF%DB%8C%D8%AC%DB%8C%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%88-%D8%A2%DB%8C%D9%81%D9%88%D9%86-8/">بررسی دیجیاتو</a>) را با همان ویژگی های آشنای همیشگی به بازار عرضه کرده است. اما اگر زرق و برق و ویژگی های تعجب برانگیز آیفون ۱۰ توجه تان را به خود جلب کرده، از شما دعوت می کنیم در ادامه برای آشنایی بیشتر با بررسی موبایل جدید و جنجالی اپل همراه باشید.</span></p>', '1510137466.jpg', 'Y', 1, '2017-11-08 14:07:47', '2017-11-13 19:33:47', '2017-11-13 19:33:47');
